Spiced Rice

Per 2c Rice (uncooked)

4tbsp nuts, slivered or diced
  Recommend: Almonds, Pecans, Walnuts
4tbsp dried fruit, diced
  Recommend: Dates, Raisins, Dried Cranberries
2tsp Cumin Seed, whole
3tsp Smoked Paprika
1tsp Turmeric, ground
1tbsp Cooking Oil

Cook Rice 
  (2c water per 1c dry uncooked rice. 
  Salt lightly, place on high heat with lid until water begins to boil, 
  turn to low and leave for 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is soft and all water has been absorbed)

In a nonstick skillet, fry cumin seed then quickly add nuts and fruit. Toss.
Add paprika and turmeric.
Toss until evenly coated with oil spices.
Spread mixture across the entire pan, lower heat to medium-low.
Add rice evenly across the pan, then press with a spatula until rice is well formed into a cohesive mass. 
Cook on low for 2-3 minutes, then let rest off heat for 2 minutes. 

Serve by placing a large plate inverted over the pan, grab the pan and plate with both hands (and potholders)
  then quickly and smoothly flip the contents out of the pan and onto the plate. 
